    <h3>What is #attached</h3>
<p>Drupal 7 introduced render arrays, which was really an expansion of the existing <a href="https://api.drupal.org/api/drupal/developer%21topics%21forms_api_reference.html/7" target="_blank">Form API</a>. One of the special elements of a render array is the <a href="https://api.drupal.org/api/drupal/developer%21topics%21forms_api_reference.html/7#attached" target="_blank">#attached</a> key. In a nutshell, it allows you to attach additional CSS or Javascript to your element. Here is a typical example that I stole straight from the <a href="https://api.drupal.org/api/drupal/modules%21color%21color.module/function/color_scheme_form/7" target="_blank">Color module</a>.</p><ul class="links inline"><li class="0 first last"><a href="http://www.metaltoad.com/blog/what-i-learned-today-drupal-attached-awesomeness" rel="tag" title="What I Learned Today: Drupal #attached Awesomeness">Read more</a></li>
